Troubleshooting Tips
Zeek not capturing traffic:

Verify network interface: ip addr show
Check Zeek is running: ps aux | grep zeek
Review Zeek logs: cat /opt/zeek/logs/current/stderr.log
No anomalies detected:

Lower anomaly threshold in configuration
Verify traffic is being generated
Check Zeek log output: cat tls-anomaly.log
Python import errors:

Reinstall packages: pip3 install --upgrade pandas numpy requests
Check Python version: python3 --version (should be 3.6+)
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated TLS anomaly detection using JA3 fingerprinting and Zeek network monitoring. You implemented fingerprint generation, configured network monitoring, and created automated alerting systems. These techniques are essential for detecting malicious TLS traffic, identifying C2 communications, and monitoring for SSL/TLS-based threats in production environments. Continue practicing by analyzing real network captures and tuning detection thresholds for your specific environment.
